('b0000001-0000-4000-8000-000400010000','Declan Forsythe','+61 417 360 982','Fukuoka','solo','2026-08-04','14:30','3D2N',1,'I did the Tokyo-Kyoto thing on my first Japan trip and loved it, but this time I deliberately flew into Fukuoka to see the Kyushu nobody back in Perth has heard of. I want to soak in Beppu''s hells, eat tonkotsu where it was invented, and sit with the heavy history of Nagasaki properly, not as a quick stop. Push the pace a bit, I get restless on slow days.','unassigned',7300,false,NULL,32500,31000,
 '{"seed_batch":"jp-01","market":"japan","person_id":"0004","unit_order":1,"unit_total":4,"trip_start_date":"2026-08-04","trip_end_date":"2026-08-10","trip_total_duration":"7D6N","origin_country":"Australia","origin_city":"Perth","ages":[29],"languages":["English (native)","Japanese (basic)"],"occasion":"Three weeks of long-service leave he refused to spend on a beach resort","budget_tier":"mid_range","daily_spend_per_pax_eur":32500,"hotel_budget_per_night_eur":31000,"hotel_budget_per_night_pax_eur":31000,"pace":"active","splurge_willingness":"one_two_splurges","dietary_restrictions":"none","mobility":"Very fit, surfs and trail-runs at home, keen for steamy hill walks and long days on foot","interests":["onsen","hidden_gems","ramen_streetfood","nature_hiking","local_culture"],"must_avoid":"The well-trodden Tokyo-Kyoto golden route; he wants the Kyushu most tourists skip","previous_visits_japan":"been_before","booking_authority":"planner_recommends","accommodation_preference":"A proper onsen ryokan in Yufuin or Beppu for the steam towns; relaxed business hotels in the cities are fine"}'::jsonb),
