('b0000001-0000-4000-8000-001300010000','Álvaro Serrano','+34 612 905 433','Osaka','honeymoon','2026-08-05','15:05','3D2N',2,'We met as architecture students in Barcelona and fell for Japan through its castles and joinery long before we fell for each other. Álvaro has wanted to stand inside Himeji Castle since university, and Núria wants to watch the sun set behind the floating torii at Miyajima on our last evening — that image is the whole reason for the route. We are not interested in a packed schedule; give us time to sit with one beautiful building rather than rush past ten. Please make sure Núria''s vegetarian meals are genuinely thought through, especially the kaiseki dinner — back home people assume Japan will leave a vegetarian hungry, and we would love to be proven gloriously wrong on our honeymoon.','unassigned',7300,false,NULL,51000,48000,
 '{"seed_batch":"jp-01","market":"japan","person_id":"0013","unit_order":1,"unit_total":4,"trip_start_date":"2026-08-05","trip_end_date":"2026-08-11","trip_total_duration":"7D6N","origin_country":"Spain","origin_city":"Barcelona","ages":[36,34],"languages":["Spanish","Catalan","English (fluent)"],"occasion":"honeymoon","budget_tier":"mid_range","daily_spend_per_pax_eur":51000,"hotel_budget_per_night_eur":96000,"hotel_budget_per_night_pax_eur":48000,"pace":"slow","splurge_willingness":"frequent","dietary_restrictions":"vegetarian","mobility":"Both fully mobile and used to long walking days exploring old towns; no limitations","interests":["history","castles","architecture","food_dining","sake_whisky"],"must_avoid":"Beef and pork on the plate (Núria is vegetarian, Álvaro eats fish); also dislikes overcrowded photo-op spots with no real history behind them","previous_visits_japan":"first_time","booking_authority":"mix","accommodation_preference":"A traditional ryokan with private onsen for the Miyajima finale; characterful boutique or 4-star hotels with a double bed in the cities, ideally near the old quarters"}'::jsonb),
