('b0000001-0000-4000-8000-001900010000','Astrid Lindqvist','+46 70 218 4490','Sapporo','group','2026-08-01','14:15','3D2N',4,'My parents grew up in a small coastal town and always said Hokkaido reminded them of home in the brochures — the lavender, the open mountains, the quiet. For their 40th anniversary my brother and I want to give them that, gently. Please make absolutely sure the kaiseki and any tasting menus can be done gluten-free; back in Sweden dining out is a constant battle and I want them to relax and just eat. A soft sunset moment somewhere beautiful where we can toast them would mean the world.','unassigned',7300,false,NULL,37000,26500,
 '{"seed_batch":"jp-01","market":"japan","person_id":"0019","unit_order":1,"unit_total":3,"trip_start_date":"2026-08-01","trip_end_date":"2026-08-06","trip_total_duration":"6D5N","origin_country":"Sweden","origin_city":"Gothenburg","ages":[66,63,38,35],"languages":["Swedish","English (fluent)","German (basic)"],"occasion":"A two-generation family trip — retired parents and their two grown children — for the parents'' 40th wedding anniversary, finally crossing Hokkaido off the list they kept on the fridge for years","budget_tier":"mid_range","daily_spend_per_pax_eur":37000,"hotel_budget_per_night_eur":106000,"hotel_budget_per_night_pax_eur":26500,"pace":"active","splurge_willingness":"frequent","dietary_restrictions":"gluten_free","mobility":"Father (66) had a hip replacement two years ago and walks well but at an unhurried pace with rest stops; no long staircases or steep scrambles. The rest are fully mobile and enjoy gentle nature walks","interests":["nature_hiking","onsen","gardens","sake_whisky","local_culture"],"must_avoid":"Rushed days and anything with lots of stairs or steep terrain for the father; also no cramped tour-bus schedules — they want slow scenic mornings","previous_visits_japan":"first_time","booking_authority":"planner_books_all","accommodation_preference":"Two comfortable rooms (one for the parents, one twin for the siblings) per stop; at least one night in a ryokan with a private or barrier-free onsen the father can use safely. Western beds preferred over floor futons for the parents"}'::jsonb),
('b0000001-0000-4000-8000-001900020000','Astrid Lindqvist','+46 70 218 4490','Otaru','group','2026-08-03',NULL,'2D1N',4,'My parents grew up in a small coastal town and always said Hokkaido reminded them of home in the brochures — the lavender, the open mountains, the quiet. For their 40th anniversary my brother and I want to give them that, gently. Please make absolutely sure the kaiseki and any tasting menus can be done gluten-free; back in Sweden dining out is a constant battle and I want them to relax and just eat. A soft sunset moment somewhere beautiful where we can toast them would mean the world.','unassigned',7300,false,NULL,37000,26500,
