('b0000001-0000-4000-8000-002000010000','Thandiwe Khumalo','+27 82 614 7308','Osaka','group','2026-08-06','14:30','3D2N',3,'We have stood in front of a chalkboard for twenty years teaching teenagers about the 20th century, and not one of us has ever stood at the Hiroshima Peace Memorial ourselves. We need to do that together, quietly, properly — it''s the real reason for this trip. Around that we want the feudal grandeur, Himeji''s white keep, the floating torii at Miyajima at high tide. Please ensure halal-friendly dining is sorted in advance; we''d rather know where we can eat than discover at the door we can''t.','unassigned',7300,false,NULL,33500,30333,
 '{"seed_batch":"jp-01","market":"japan","person_id":"0020","unit_order":1,"unit_total":4,"trip_start_date":"2026-08-06","trip_end_date":"2026-08-12","trip_total_duration":"7D6N","origin_country":"South Africa","origin_city":"Cape Town","ages":[41,39,43],"languages":["English (native)","Zulu","Afrikaans (conversational)"],"occasion":"Three friends who met as junior history teachers two decades ago, now taking the bucket-list trip they''ve talked about in every staffroom since — built around Japan''s wartime and feudal history","budget_tier":"mid_range","daily_spend_per_pax_eur":33500,"hotel_budget_per_night_eur":91000,"hotel_budget_per_night_pax_eur":30333,"pace":"active","splurge_willingness":"one_two_splurges","dietary_restrictions":"halal","mobility":"All three fully mobile and fit; happy to walk all day, climb castle keeps and ferry hop, just want comfortable shoes and the odd coffee break","interests":["history","castles","architecture","food_dining","local_culture"],"must_avoid":"Pork and alcohol-required venues (halal); also wants substance over selfie-spots — skip places that are only there for the photo with no story behind them","previous_visits_japan":"first_time","booking_authority":"mix","accommodation_preference":"Three single rooms or a triple, in clean comfortable mid-range hotels near the stations so we can move easily; one nicer stay with a view of Hiroshima or Himeji castle would be a wonderful treat"}'::jsonb),
